  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO AMEND CHAPTER 958, LOCAL AND PRIVATE LAWS OF 2018, AS AMENDED BY CHAPTER 921, LOCAL AND PRIVATE LAWS OF 2022, TO EXTEND THE DATE OF REPEAL FROM JULY 1, 2026, TO JULY 1, 2030, ON THE PROVISION OF LAW THAT AUTHORIZES THE GOVERNING AUTHORITIES OF THE CITY OF MOSS POINT, MISSISSIPPI, TO LEVY AN ADDITIONAL SALES TAX OF NOT MORE THAN TWO PERCENT UPON THE GROSS PROCEEDS DERIVED FROM THE SALE OF PREPARED FOODS BY RESTAURANTS IN THE CITY; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
